ngs":["(1997: 122;2010: NA)","Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Bo Young, Chae, Chong Hwan, Dong Kun, Ho, Hwan, Hyun, Jong, Jung, Ki Soon, Kwang.  Korean Min, Chong, Chol, Jung Ho, Myong, Sa, Sung Kyun.","Korean (오; Chinese character: 吳): historically, there were two Chinese characters for the O surname, but by the late Koryŏ period (14th century  AD ), one of them had disappeared. Some records indicate that there are as many as 210 different clans for the remaining character, but only sixteen can be positively documented. All sixteen of these clans originate from the same ancestor, O Ch’ŏm (吳 瞻), who migrated to Korea from China during the reign of Shilla's King Chijŭng (500–514  AD ). <i>O</i> is a common surname throughout Korea. Compare   Oh  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Oh","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Sung, Jung, Yong, Chang, Kwang, Sang, Dong, Hyun, Jae, Jin, Kyung, Jong, Chong, Chung, Byung, Jeong, Pyong, Myong, Hak, Jin Hwan, Sook, Yeong, Choon.","Korean: variant of   O  .","Japanese: variant of <b>Ō</b> (see   O  )."]}]},{"name":"Mulloy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brigid, Padraic, Seamus.","Irish (mainly Mayo): variant of   Molloy  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Molloy","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Brigid, Eamon, Fintan, Brid, Caitlin, Colm, Cormac, Dermot, Ethna, Kevin Patrick, Kieran.","Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Maolmhuaidh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Maolmhuadh</i>’, a personal name based on <i>maol</i> ‘youth, chieftain’ and <i>muad</i> ‘noble, glorious’."]}]},{"name":"Mór","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name from <i>mór</i> ‘large, great’. This was the commonest of all girls’ names in late medieval Ireland, and has continued in use in both Ireland and Scotland to the present day."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mór O Mulloy was born about 0990, in Munster, Ireland, her father, Gilla-Brigte Ua Maíl Muaid of Cenél Fiachrach, was 47 and her mother, BRIDGET O'MULLOY, was 45. She had at least 4 sons with Tadc Mac Briain. She died in 1018, in Ireland, at the age of 29."},"et":{"about 0990–1018":"umbes 0990–1018","0990–1018":"0990–1018","0984–1023":"0984–1023","1008–1086":"1008–1086","1009–1086":"1009–1086","1011–1064":"1011–1064","1013–1073":"1013–1073","0944–1018":"0944–1018","0947–Female":"0947–Surnud","1011":"1011","1064":"1064","1086":"1086","1073":"1073","1008":"1008","1018":"1018","0984":"0984","1013":"1013","0990":"0990","about 1008":"umbes 1008","1023":"1023","0947":"0947","about 0990":"umbes 0990","1009":"1009","0944":"0944","Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Iirimaa","Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Munster, Ireland":"Munster, Iirimaa","Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Iirimaa","Offally, Lancaster, Ireland":"County Offaly, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"about 0990–1018":"noin 0990–1018","0990–1018":"0990–1018","0984–1023":"0984–1023","1008–1086":"1008–1086","1009–1086":"1009–1086","1011–1064":"1011–1064","1013–1073":"1013–1073","0944–1018":"0944–1018","0947–Female":"0947–Kuollut","1011":"1011","1064":"1064","1086":"1086","1073":"1073","1008":"1008","1018":"1018","0984":"0984","1013":"1013","0990":"0990","about 1008":"noin 1008","1023":"1023","0947":"0947","about 0990":"noin 0990","1009":"1009","0944":"0944","Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Irlanti","Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti","Munster, Ireland":"Munster, Irlanti","Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Irlanti","Offally, Lancaster, Ireland":"County Offaly, Irlanti"},"fr":{"about 0990–1018":"environ 0990–1018","0990–1018":"0990–1018","0984–1023":"0984–1023","1008–1086":"1008–1086","1009–1086":"1009–1086","1011–1064":"1011–1064","1013–1073":"1013–1073","0944–1018":"0944–1018","0947–Female":"09